Most Japanese Stocks Rise, Reversing Declines: Isuzu Motors, Toshiba Jump

-- B y   A k i k o   I k e d a
-- 
2011-04-14T05:18:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/japanese-stocks-fall-as-yen-strengthens-honda-motor-canon-olympus-drop.html
Most Japanese stocks rose,
reversing earlier declines, led by Isuzu Motors Ltd. and after
Toshiba Corp. said its profit may beat its earlier forecast.  Isuzu surged 6.5 percent, the most in the  Nikkei 225  Stock
Average, even after it denied after a report that Volkswagen AG
is considering taking a stake in the company. Toshiba, a nuclear
reactor supplier, advanced 2.5 percent as the company’s
President Norio Sasaki said it may report full-year net income
that’s higher than what it had forecast in January.  Nomura
Holdings Inc. (8604)  sank 1.4 percent after Credit Suisse Group AG cut
its rating on the company.  The Nikkei 225 rose 0.1 percent to 9,654.02 as of 2:16 p.m.
in  Tokyo  after falling as much as 0.9 percent. The broader Topix
index gained 0.3 percent to 846.86 The Topix lost 9.3 percent
through yesterday from March 10, the day before the earthquake
and tsunami that devastated  Japan ’s northeast coast and crippled
a Tokyo Electric Power Co.’s plant in Fukushima.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Akiko Ikeda in Tokyo at 
 iakiko@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at 
 ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 